# CombatMode Change Checklist

Before finalizing code changes, run this checklist.

- API checks: verify changed WoW API usage with MCP (`lookup_api`, `list_deprecated`, `get_event`, `get_enum`).
- Module ownership: keep edits in the feature/config module that owns behavior.
- Combat safety: guard protected paths and avoid insecure changes in combat.
- State symmetry: for mouselook/CVars/bindings, ensure enable/apply has matching disable/cleanup.
- Config wiring: new setting has defaults, correct DB scope, and options UI integration.
- Regression pass: cover slash commands, keybind flows, and mainline runtime path for touched feature.
- Lint/format pass (changed files): run `pre-commit run --files <changed lua files>`.
- Tool-specific debug checks when needed: `stylua --check <paths>` and `selene --config selene.toml <paths>`.
- Run repo-wide formatting/lint only for release prep or explicit maintainer request: `pre-commit run --all-files`.
